essentially removing the danger of war. people and habits[edit] china is a very diverse place with large variations in culture, language, customs and economic levels. the economic landscape is particularly diverse. the major cities such as beijing, guangzhou and shanghai are modern and comparatively wealthy. however, about 50% of chinese still live in rural areas even though only 10% of china's land is arable. hundreds of millions of rural residents still farm with manual labour or draft animals. some 200 to 300 million former peasants have migrated to townships and cities in search of work. government estimates for 2005 reported 